node.text:
In effort to relieve myself of the heaviness of unexpressed grief and the frustration of stagnation, I took a fairly large dose of psilocybin mushrooms.  Two main components - jaw dropping wonder at never before considered color combinations and profound grief about my mentor and friend @frenchycannoli.  My emotions ran the gamut for five and a half hours.  My friendship with @tali_lala strengthened as she sat for me while I journeyed to far off planes.  As the observer, I remember being tickled about being in several places at once and the notion of this disembodied (and yet still on my phone screen) voice being totally normal. 

Here's to many, many, many explorations. 

#psychedelics #cannabis #grief

All we need is love....and grace.  When we realize that we have been going awry and we make the decision to change, we must give ourselves grace for the actions we took in the past.  That was the past.  Our responsibility is to imbue the present with our presence and our right-minded intentions.  Shoulda, coulda, woulda tears down the delicate trellis that is the guide for getting us out of the mess we find ourselves.  When we deny ourselves the grace and space to be human, we become forever prisoners to our old selves.

So you fell off...so what!  Did you get back up again with eyes looking forward and a confident stride to boot?  Good!  You are on your way to greatness.  After all, today is a great day to be awesome.

#motivation #love #grace #empowered #selflove #selfimprovement #cannabis #microdosing #psychedelics #fitness #selfcare

Life is way too short to deny ourselves the extreme pleasure and fulfillment of being ourselves.  We shy away from jumping into our deepest desires for fear that other people would sneer at  the perceived 'weirdness' as well as our devotion to that very notion of outside derision.

Our joy is our place of healing, transformation, and growth.  We do our entire bodies a good service when we immerse ourselves in our truths.  in the truth there is inner and outer peace and wellness.

Why would we ever deny ourselves that?

#joy #peace #peaceofmind

A message from last year...the attitudes of those around us bleed into yourue consciousness and eventually change who we are...

____
The quality of your circle is a great indication of who you will become.  We are all influenced by our closest peers.  Our energies commingle, so our interactions always leave us just a bit changed - for better or worse.

Good people will change the trajectory of your life.  Awful people (often disguised as the snarky, pull a fast one, aloof and conceited "asshole" friends) are just asshole acquaintances...and they will drag you down.

It seems so simple, and yet people screw themselves over all the time. "Nice" types pride themselves on their forgiveness while they hold the door open for snakes.  If you cannot respect yourself enough to elevate beyond the low energies seeping off fake friends, you will soon be wallowing in the shit too...

#cannabiscommunity

node.text:
It seems we are always in silent competition with idealized versions of our peers.  Constant comparison weakens our belief in ourselves.  We become our hardest critics and our worst enemies. 

But everyone progresses as they should; given their unique circumstances.  Far too often we are looking at others' sizable gains in one way and we are neglecting to appreciate our own substantial gains.

It is not a race.
 ...and if it is, it certainly is not a sprint.

We we focus on ourselves, we intensify our impact.  We have confidence in our competence to pursue our INDIVIDUAL goals.
🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟
#growyourown #cannabis #cannabiscommunity

I delight in the Beach Days I have with @sarahjain420, sinsemilla (cannabis without seeds), and psilocybin (from the psychedelic mushrooms).

Our only aim is to enjoy the moment.  Every beach day is different, but the running motifs are self acceptance and slowing down. 

The aggressive surf soaked our stuff and pushed us into the rocks, but the combination of the 0.125g and multiple puffs on my glass chillum kept me in the flow.

I even got on the boogie board with my new friend JamieandErick.

A nice and easy beach day overall.

For the very first time, April 20th was a fearless celebration in New York; devoid of the constant worry of impending legal doom.  After smoking fat joints in Times Square in full few of the cops, @seanscott (my AMAZING photographer/videographer), @mzladyhoneyjane, @ceegreenz, and I made our way down to the @happymunkey_ party and we never left. Check the vid to see why.

Educationis crucial.  Entertainment matters.  When the mashup hits, it's lit..and Vlad and Ramón know how to make it fuego.

I am slated to be back in NYC in 2 weeks.  Who's down for Chillin' with the Chillum?

⚡⚡⚡
Work like you are getting paid today.  Live and love like there is no tomorrow.
⚡⚡⚡

#cannabis #culture #lifestyle

Even though I play totally sober so therefore not #fueledbythc, I always catch a good vibe when I play for my plants. They don't speak, but the plants always manage to communicate that they appreciate the classical music.  I have played my tenor pan for over 30 years and I am energized every single time.  Even when I play sloppily (yes, I must practice), the plants and I all benefit.  I have actually had this pan in this room for over a month, but it has sat forlornly in the corner of the tent.  No longer content to be complacent about my gifts, I am back to practicing. 

But now...a smoke. 😆

As we gear up for our HIGHEST holiday, I consider what keeps me most uplifted.  For all of the dank #cannabis in the world, nothing makes my spirit soar like playing my steelpan.  And as much as I love to play classical music solo, there is NOTHING quite like playing in a band.  And when I play next to true genius, I feel SOMETHING up and down my spine.

No high is quite like it.

This clip is from 2018, playing Michael Kernahan's arrangement for  of @machelmontano's "Take it Slow." Rather than playing with our own band, 21st Century Steel Orchestra, my good friend @caribpapi868 and I played with Phase III Pan Stars for the Miami Panorama Competition. 
___
What makes you swoon?  What brings you to the place of sheer elation such that nothing stops you from doing it?  What makes your heart burst in its seams?

Whatever it is...do it!  Do it so that your spirit may soar!
___
#music  #steelpan #art #joy #cannabiscommunity

HASH CLASS IN DC THIS THURSDAY w/ @dcscroger  and @natlcannabisfest *link in bio*
___________
60 sec tech:
There's a tendency to believe that short washes are necessary to make cleaner resin output.

I believe that yield has a tendency to suffer greatly in effort to get the cleanest wash possible.

However the two considerations are not mutually exclusive.

You can get consistently good yields by having the right strain, very cold water, the right portion of material to water and ice, and significant amount of time spun.  People are often  concerned about resin turning green.

Resin will turn green, especially if starting with fresh frozen, if the water is not cold enough. Resin will turn green if there's too much ice in the machine. But if everything is in balance, material can be pushed to its end and return really good looking product without sacrificing the amount that is produced.

I am consistently looking for 12-16% yield on dry material (and 4-6+% on fresh frozen). My aim is to get everything possible off the plant.

By the way, the fifth wash was a beaut too 😊

Material:  Purple Punch from @missionnurseries

Where do your yields lie?  Do you think you can push your material further?

Bubble hash and hash rosin class going down in DC on August 26th!

In conjunction with @natlcannabisfest, I along with @DCScroger will be hosting a workshop that is going to teach you how to take your fire flower and turn it into amazingly dank resin and rosin.

We will teach you how to 
1) Choose the right cultivar
2) Prepare and handle material
3) Wash cleanly and effectively
4) Dry thoroughly
5) Press frenchy tech style
6) Squish into hash rosin
7) Create hash rosin derivatives

And of course there will be lots of Chillin' with the Chillum.  So come out and join us.

DM @natlcannabisfest for more info

node.text:
People are often under the mistaken assumption that all #solventless #hash must be kept in the fridge or the freezer. For granular sieved or freeze dried bubble hash whose color you want to retain, the proper procedure is to keep it in a cold refrigerator (or freezer) that is not opened often. Pressed hash, with its color already altered by heat and manipulation, has the capacity to sit at room temperature and not change. The outer shell of the hash is all that is subject to oxidation. And some #cannabis resin is unable to be pressed properly. Rather, at mild, ambient temperatures, the heads melt together into a sappy texture. Clean heads only. Well dried heads only.

node.text:
When I press resin for preservation and aging, I am looking for proof that the collection was a clean and proper one.  Everything about the state of the resin is revealed after pressing it  with the hot bottle.

The sheen indicates that:
1.The resin is well dried.  Moist resin is likely nucleate after a fairly short time, leaving the skin of the hash matte and somewhat crumbly.

2. The resin has little particulate.  The sheen only forms when the press is very smooth and even.  Unmeltable plant particulate prevents the creation of a homogeneous mass, so the polish is never achieved.

3. The resin has a lot of oil.  High quality resin will melt easily and thoroughly.  It is malleable and moldable and maintains a tight, plastic-like shell.

node.text:
Harvest time has come and my smile could not be wider.

After a devastating heat wave of my own doing very early on during which my tent reached 113 degrees 🙄, it was reassuring to see the plants turn a corner weeks ago and begin to come into their own.  Now at the end of week 9, their verdant greens are pale yellows and burnt oranges.  Seems like they're ready...

A few checks with the loupe and we are out.  How about a joint to celebrate?  I think I shall indeed indulge. She is full of magic and bliss  She has my heart...

#growyourown #organic #cannabis

node.text:
Growing your own cannabis is the sweetest vibe.  Your garden need not be award winning or perfect for magazine spreads in order to be worthwhile.  Cannabis is a powerful, but gentle spirit that guides even as it grows.  We partake in its wisdom long before we partake in the smoke/edible/tincture.

Patience, mindfulness, compassion, and responsibility are always at the forefront when caring for a #cannabis garden.  Wait, how could I forget #love!

node.text:
My second favorite time in the growing timeline...harvest.  This is also a bittersweet time as I lose good friends in the process...

But aren't these colors on these Banana Split OG crosses lovely?  Not much longer for these canna beauties.  Everytime I walk into the tent, I am blasted with a vast array of smells.  I am so very lucky to be alive at THIS very time.  Everyday is an adventure.

Please comment 👇🏾the times when are you particularly aware how lucky you are (whether you grow cannabis or not). ♥️

But if you DO have the capacity, please do #growyourown.  We need as many farmers as possible.

🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟🌟

node.text:
In effort to relieve myself of the heaviness of unexpressed grief and the frustration of stagnation, I took a fairly large dose of psilocybin mushrooms.  Two main components - jaw dropping wonder at never before considered color combinations and profound grief about my mentor and friend @frenchycannoli.  My emotions ran the gamut for five and a half hours.  My friendship with @tali_lala strengthened as she sat for me while I journeyed to far off planes.  As the observer, I remember being tickled about being in several places at once and the notion of this disembodied (and yet still on my phone screen) voice being totally normal. 

Here's to many, many, many explorations. 

#psychedelics #cannabis #grief
